   <DIV style="  display: block; ">
    <DIV style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt;font-weight: normal;  padding-left: 0pt; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; background-color: white; padding-top: 9px; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 10pt;">
     <P style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt;text-align: left; margin: 0pt; padding: 0pt; ">
      <TABLE cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0" style=" font-size: 10pt; width: 100%; ">

   <DIV style="  display: block; ">
    <P><FONT style="font-weight: normal;  font-size: 9pt;"><FONT style=" display: inline-block; text-align: left; width: 50%; font-size: 9pt;">SEE NOTES TO FUND'S INVESTMENTS</FONT><FONT style=" display: inline-block; text-align: right; width: 50%; font-size: 9pt;">23</FONT></FONT></P>
   </DIV>
  <HR>
   <P style="page-break-before:always; margin:0pt; margin-bottom: 28pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt;"></P>
  </DIV>

  <DIV style="display:block; width: 98%;">
   <DIV style="  display: block; ">
    <DIV style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt;font-weight: normal;  padding-left: 0pt; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; background-color: white; padding-top: 9px; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 10pt;">
     <P style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt;font-weight: bold;  padding-left: 0pt; text-align: left; background-color: white; padding-top: 12px; line-height: 1.1; font-size: 16pt;">Notes to Fund's investments (unaudited)</P>

     <P style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; text-align: left; background-color: white; padding-top: 4.5px; line-height: 1.4; font-size: 9pt;"><B>Security valuation. </B>Investments are stated at value as of the scheduled close of regular
trading on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE), normally at 4:00 <FONT style="font-variant: small-caps; ">p.m.</FONT>, Eastern Time. In case of emergency or other disruption resulting in
the NYSE not opening for trading or the NYSE closing at a time other
than the regularly scheduled close, the net asset value may be
determined as of the regularly scheduled close of the NYSE pursuant
to the fund's Valuation Policies and Procedures.</P>

     <P style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; text-align: left; background-color: white; padding-top: 4.5px; line-height: 1.4; font-size: 9pt;">In order to value the securities, the fund uses the following
valuation techniques: Debt obligations are valued based on the
evaluated prices provided by an independent pricing vendor or from
broker-dealers. Independent pricing vendors utilize matrix pricing
which takes into account factors such as institutional-size trading
in similar groups of securities, yield, quality, coupon rate,
maturity, type of issue, trading characteristics and other market
data, as well as broker supplied prices. Equity securities held by
the fund are typically valued at the last sale price or official
closing price on the exchange or principal market where the security
trades. In the event there were no sales during the day or closing
prices are not available, the securities are valued using the last
available bid&nbsp;price.</P>

     <P style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; text-align: left; background-color: white; padding-top: 4.5px; line-height: 1.4; font-size: 9pt;">In certain instances, the Pricing Committee may determine to value
equity securities using prices obtained from another exchange or
market if trading on the exchange or market on which prices are
typically obtained did not open for trading as scheduled, or if
trading closed earlier than scheduled, and trading occurred as normal
on another exchange or&nbsp;market.</P>

     <P style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; text-align: left; background-color: white; padding-top: 4.5px; line-height: 1.4; font-size: 9pt;">Other portfolio securities and assets, for which reliable market
quotations are not readily available, are valued at fair value as
determined in good faith by the fund's Pricing Committee following
procedures established by the Board of Trustees. The frequency with
which these fair valuation procedures are used cannot be predicted
and fair value of securities may differ significantly from the value
that would have been used had a ready market for such securities
existed.</P>

     <P style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; text-align: left; background-color: white; padding-top: 4.5px; line-height: 1.4; font-size: 9pt;">The fund uses a three-tier hierarchy to prioritize the pricing
assumptions, referred to as inputs, used in valuation techniques to
measure fair value. Level 1 includes securities valued using quoted
prices in active markets for identical securities. Level 2 includes
securities valued using other significant observable inputs.
Observable inputs may include quoted prices for similar securities,
interest rates, prepayment speeds and credit risk. Prices for
securities valued using these inputs are received from independent
pricing vendors and brokers and are based on an evaluation of the
inputs described. Level 3 includes securities valued using
significant unobservable inputs when market prices are not readily
available or reliable, including the fund's own assumptions in
determining the fair value of investments. Factors used in
determining value may include market or issuer specific events or
trends, changes in interest rates and credit quality. The inputs or
methodology used for valuing securities are not necessarily an
indication of the risks associated with investing in those
securities. Changes in valuation techniques and related inputs may
result in transfers into or out of an assigned level within the
disclosure hierarchy.</P>

     <P style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; text-align: left; background-color: white; padding-top: 4.5px; line-height: 1.4; font-size: 9pt;">The following is a summary of the values by input classification of
the fund's investments as of <FONT style="padding-top: 0px; ">February 28, 2017</FONT>, by major security category or&nbsp;type:</P>

         <TD style=" background-color: white; background-color: white; color: black; padding-top: 2px; line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: bottom; border-bottom: 1pt black solid; text-align: right; font-size: 8pt; "><B>$36,804,461</B></TD>

         <TD style=" background-color: white; background-color: white; color: black; padding-top: 2px; line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: bottom; border-bottom: 1pt black solid; text-align: right; font-size: 8pt; "><B>$6,032,775,903</B></TD>

         <TD style=" background-color: white; background-color: white; color: black; padding-top: 2px; line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: bottom; border-bottom: 1pt black solid; text-align: right; font-size: 8pt; "><B>&#151;</B></TD>
        </TR>
       </TABLE>
     </P>

     <P style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; text-align: left; background-color: white; padding-top: 4.5px; line-height: 1.4; font-size: 9pt;"><B>Repurchase agreements. </B>The fund may enter into repurchase agreements. When the fund enters
into a repurchase agreement, it receives collateral that is held in a
segregated account by the fund's custodian, or for tri-party
repurchase agreements, collateral is held at a third-party custodian
bank in a segregated account for the benefit of the fund. The
collateral amount is marked-to-market and monitored on a daily basis
to ensure that the collateral held is in an amount not less than the
principal amount of the repurchase agreement plus any accrued
interest. Collateral received by the fund for repurchase agreements
is disclosed in the Fund's investments as part of the caption related
to the repurchase agreement.</P>

     <P style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; text-align: left; background-color: white; padding-top: 4.5px; line-height: 1.4; font-size: 9pt;">Repurchase agreements are typically governed by the terms and
conditions of the Master Repurchase Agreement and/or Global Master
Repurchase Agreement (collectively, MRA). Upon an event of default,
the non-defaulting party may close out all transactions traded under
the MRA and net amounts owed. Absent an event of default, assets and
liabilities resulting from repurchase agreements are not offset. In
the event of a default by the counterparty, realization of the
collateral proceeds could be delayed, during which time the
collateral value may decline or the counterparty may have
insufficient assets to pay back claims resulting from close-out of
the transactions.</P>

     <P style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; text-align: left; background-color: white; padding-top: 4.5px; line-height: 1.4; font-size: 9pt;">For additional information on the fund's significant accounting
policies, please refer to the fund's most recent semiannual or annual
shareholder report.</P>

and procedures as conducted within 90 days of the filing date of this Form N-Q, the registrant's principal executive officer and
principal accounting officer have concluded that those disclosure controls and procedures provide reasonable assurance that the
material information required to be disclosed by the registrant on this report is recorded, processed, summarized and reported
within the time periods specified in the Securities and Exchange Commission's rules and forms.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-right: 0; margin-left: 0"><B><U>CERTIFICATION</U></B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-right: 0; margin-left: 0">I, Andrew Arnott, certify that:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">1. I have reviewed this report on Form N-Q of John Hancock
Sovereign Bond Fund (the &#8220;registrant&#8221;);</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">2. Based on my knowledge, this report does not contain any
untrue statement of a material fact or omit to state a material fact necessary to make the statements made, in light of the circumstances
under which such statements were made, not misleading with respect to the period covered by this report;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">3. Based on my knowledge, the schedules of investments included
in this report fairly present in all material respects the investments of the registrant as of the end of the fiscal quarter for
which the report is filed;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">4. The registrant&#8217;s other certifying officer and I are
responsible for establishing and maintaining disclosure controls and procedures (as defined in Rule 30a-3(c) under the Investment
Company Act of 1940) and internal control over financial reporting (as defined in Rule 30a-3(d) under the Investment Company Act
of 1940) for the registrant and have:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">(a) Designed such disclosure controls and procedures, or caused
such disclosure controls and procedures to be designed under our supervision, to ensure that material information relating to the
registrant, including its consolidated subsidiaries, is made known to us by others within those entities, particularly during the
period in which this report is being prepared;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">(b) Designed such internal control over financial reporting,
or caused such internal control over financial reporting to be designed under our supervision, to provide reasonable assurance
regarding the reliability of financial reporting and the preparation of financial statements for external purposes in accordance
with generally accepted accounting principles;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">(c) Evaluated the effectiveness of the registrant&#8217;s
disclosure controls and procedures and presented in this report our conclusions about the effectiveness of the disclosure controls
and procedures, as of a date within 90 days prior to the filing date of this report, based on such evaluation; and</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">(d) Disclosed in this report any change in the registrant&#8217;s
internal control over financial reporting that occurred during the registrant&#8217;s most recent fiscal quarter that has materially
affected, or is reasonably likely to materially affect, the registrant&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting; and</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">5. The registrant&#8217;s other certifying officer and I have
disclosed to the registrant&#8217;s auditors and the audit committee of the registrant&#8217;s board of directors (or persons performing
the equivalent functions):</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">(a) All significant deficiencies and material weaknesses in
the design or operation of internal control over financial reporting which are reasonably likely to adversely affect the registrant&#8217;s
ability to record, process, summarize, and report financial information; and</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">(b) Any fraud, whether or not material, that involves management
or other employees who have a significant role in the registrant&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0 19.45pt 0 0.25in; text-align: left; text-indent: -0.25in">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0 19.45pt 0 0.25in; text-align: left; text-indent: -0.25in">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0 19.45pt 0 0.25in; text-align: left; text-indent: -0.25in">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0 19.45pt -16px 0.25in; text-align: left; text-indent: -0.25in">Date:
<U>April 19, 2017</U></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin-right: 0; margin-left: 0">I, Charles A. Rizzo, certify that:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">1. I have reviewed this report on Form N-Q of John Hancock
Sovereign Bond Fund (the &#8220;registrant&#8221;);</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">2. Based on my knowledge, this report does not contain any
untrue statement of a material fact or omit to state a material fact necessary to make the statements made, in light of the circumstances
under which such statements were made, not misleading with respect to the period covered by this report;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">3. Based on my knowledge, the schedules of investments included
in this report fairly present in all material respects the investments of the registrant as of the end of the fiscal quarter for
which the report is filed;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">4. The registrant&#8217;s other certifying officer and I are
responsible for establishing and maintaining disclosure controls and procedures (as defined in Rule 30a-3(c) under the Investment
Company Act of 1940) and internal control over financial reporting (as defined in Rule 30a-3(d) under the Investment Company Act
of 1940) for the registrant and have:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">(a) Designed such disclosure controls and procedures, or caused
such disclosure controls and procedures to be designed under our supervision, to ensure that material information relating to the
registrant, including its consolidated subsidiaries, is made known to us by others within those entities, particularly during the
period in which this report is being prepared;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">(b) Designed such internal control over financial reporting,
or caused such internal control over financial reporting to be designed under our supervision, to provide reasonable assurance
regarding the reliability of financial reporting and the preparation of financial statements for external purposes in accordance
with generally accepted accounting principles;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Arial Narrow, Helvetica, Sans-Serif; margin: 0">(c) Evaluated the effectiveness of the registrant&#8217;s

and procedures, as of a date within 90 days prior to the filing date of this report, based on such evaluation; and</P>

internal control over financial reporting that occurred during the registrant&#8217;s most recent fiscal quarter that has materially
affected, or is reasonably likely to materially affect, the registrant&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting; and</P>
